    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1976-09-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1976-09-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="293"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d293">
                <head>293. Memorandum From Director of Central Intelligence <persName
                        corresp="#p_BGHW_1">Bush</persName> to Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d293fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Executive Registry, Job 79M00467A, Box 23, Folder 427. Secret; Sensitive. A
                        copy was sent to <persName corresp="#p_SB_2">Scowcroft</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1976-09-07">September 7, 1976</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Additional Information Concerning <gloss target="#t_PLO_1">PLO</gloss>
                        Desire to Enter Political Negotiations with the United States
                        Government</item>
                </list>
                <p>1. The following provides additional background supplementing my memorandum [<hi
                        rend="italic">1½ lines not declassified</hi>]</p>
                <p>2. [<hi rend="italic">1 line not declassified</hi>] Palestine Liberation
                    Organization (<gloss target="#t_PLO_1">PLO</gloss>) Chairman <persName
                        corresp="#p_AY_2">Yasir ’Arafat</persName> has been thinking for almost a
                    year of attempting to establish a totally secret “pre-dialogue” channel to the
                    United States (U.S.) Government. [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not
                        declassified</hi>] disillusionment with the Syrian relationship has made the
                        <gloss target="#t_PLO_1">PLO</gloss> far more ready to compromise than it
                    was in the past. The mood within the <gloss target="#t_PLO_1">PLO</gloss>
                    leadership is definitely one of trying to resolve its own problems through
                    compromise and to resist exploitation of the <gloss target="#t_PLO_1"
                        >PLO</gloss> by other Arab states for their own purposes.</p>
                <p>3. [<hi rend="italic">8 lines not declassified</hi>] Nevertheless, [<hi
                        rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] <persName
                        corresp="#p_AY_2">’Arafat</persName> has political negotiations with the
                    U.S. very much in mind, if they can be arranged.</p>
                <p>4. Finally, [<hi rend="italic">less than 1 line not declassified</hi>] <persName
                        corresp="#p_AY_2">’Arafat</persName> is suspicious of the tendency of some
                    Arab states, such as Egypt and Tunisia, to project themselves as intermediaries
                    between the <gloss target="#t_PLO_1">PLO</gloss> and the U.S. <persName
                        corresp="#p_AY_2">’Arafat</persName> judges that such efforts are patently
                    self-serving and should be avoided.</p>
                <p>5. A copy of this memorandum is being sent to the Honorable <persName
                        corresp="#p_SB_2">Brent Scowcroft</persName>, Assistant to the President for
                    National Security Affairs. No other dissemination is being made.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_BGHW_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BGHW_1">George Bush</persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d293fn2">Printed from a copy that indicates <persName
                                corresp="#p_BGHW_1">Bush</persName> signed the original.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
